         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden ¶ 23/4/70 ¶  ¶ Will you be so kind, dear Mr Wadsworth, to apprize his Excellency Viscount Canterbury of my wish, to connect his honored name as a lasting mark of homage with one o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.04.23e</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Robert Wadsworth</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">M70/19, unit 26, VPRS 1096 inward correspondence, VA 466 Governor, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/4/70</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you be so kind, dear Mr Wadsworth, to apprize his Excellency Viscount Canterbury of my wish, to connect his honored name as a lasting mark of homage with one of the 3 magnificent Palms recently discovered in Lord Howes Island,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Kentia canteburyana</seg>. See B70.04.01, p. 101.</p>
               </note> one other being dedicated to Earl Belmere,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Belmore? M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Kentia Belmoreana</seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">K. Mooreana</seg>, both also from Lord Howe Island, in the same issue of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg> (pp. 99 and 101 respectively).</p>
               </note> in whose colonial territory the discovery was made. A small plant of the <name key="Kentia%20Canterburiana">Kentia Canterburiana</name> is in my conservatory, and I hope to secure one for his Lordship from Mr Ch. Moore.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your very regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have written the description of this magnificent plant for the current number of my Fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Viscount Canterbury: 'Inform Dr Von Mueller that I accept with gratification his offer to confer my name on a recently discovered Palm Tree | <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Cy</hi>
                     </seg> | May 12 1870'. The same day, Wadsworth added 'Done'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kentia%20Canterburiana">Kentia Canterburiana</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
